---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import me from '../assets/me.png';
---

<Layout
  title="Jeremiah Church - Technical founder"
  description="Technical founder. Building Comma Compliance - the modern communications ingestion layer for regulated organizations. Also: cars, solar, home automation, tinkering."
>
  <section class="mb-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row-reverse sm:items-start sm:gap-8 gap-6">
      <Image
        src={me}
        alt="Jeremiah Church"
        width={320}
        height={252}
        widths={[160, 240, 320]}
        sizes="(min-width: 640px) 160px, 140px"
        loading="eager"
        class="w-[140px] sm:w-[160px] h-auto rounded-lg object-cover shrink-0"
      />
      <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-3">
          San Francisco &middot; Chattanooga &middot; hi@jeremiah.church
        </p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-6">
          Jeremiah Church.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-ink)]/90 max-w-[55ch]">
          Technical founder. I build software for regulated industries, race cars in my
          spare time, and run a solar-powered shop that doubles as a home lab.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
      Now
    </h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-[17px] leading-relaxed max-w-[60ch]">
      <p>
        Building <a href="https://commacompliance.com">Comma Compliance</a> - WhatsApp,
        Signal, iMessage, and 40+ channel archiving for SEC and FINRA-regulated firms.
      </p>
      <p>
        Shipping <a href="https://github.com/comma-compliance/arc-relay">Arc Relay</a>,
        our open-source MCP control plane. Auth, policy, middleware, and audit trail for
        any AI agent talking to any tool.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
      Work
    </h2>
    <ul class="space-y-6 max-w-[60ch]">
      <li>
        <p class="font-medium">
          Comma Compliance
          <span class="text-[var(--color-muted)] font-normal">- founder &amp; CEO, 2024 - present</span>
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-[15px]">
          Modern communications ingestion for regulated work. Customers across financial
          services, multinational POCs in flight.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="font-medium">
          Finance Forge
          <span class="text-[var(--color-muted)] font-normal">- 2020 - 2021, acquired</span>
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-[15px]">
          Fintech tooling. Built, sold, and handed off.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="font-medium">
          Syncta
          <span class="text-[var(--color-muted)] font-normal">- founder, acquired 2019</span>
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-[15px]">
          B2B SaaS for backflow testing compliance. Plumbing, literally. Built from zero,
          sold to Watts Water, ran the integration after.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="font-medium">
          Fiserv and many others
          <span class="text-[var(--color-muted)] font-normal">- 2011 - 2018</span>
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-[15px]">
          Plumbing, figuratively. Payments, core banking, and the unglamorous pipework
          underneath a lot of the financial services you use every day.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
      Off the clock
    </h2>
    <ul class="space-y-6 max-w-[60ch]">
      <li>
        <p class="font-medium">Cars &amp; motorsport</p>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-[15px]">
          Putting LS's into anything and everything. Crashing scratch-builts on
          hillclimbs. Too many project cars collecting dust in the shop.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="font-medium">Solar &amp; home automation</p>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-[15px]">
          64 kW of solar, 136 kWh of lithium, CT clamps on every circuit. We only pull
          from the grid when the three-phase buck generator needs to start for the CNCs.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p class="font-medium">Tinkering</p>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)] text-[15px]">
          Reverse-engineering firmware, 3D printing, CNC, and the occasional
          ill-advised smart-home integration. I have opinions on ESPHome.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-4">
    <h2 class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-muted)] mb-4">
      Contact
    </h2>
    <p class="max-w-[60ch]">
      Email is the fastest way: <a href="mailto:hi@jeremiah.church"><code class="font-mono text-[15px]">hi@jeremiah.church</code></a>.
    </p>
    <p class="max-w-[60ch] mt-4">
      I've had the same phone number since the dawn of time, and I'll have it until I
      die. If you have it, call me.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
